{
  "texts": [
    "For instance, V1 (Infrastructure Implementation) was ranked 3rd using NBC, but it climbed to 1st with LR, whereas V2 (Security in 6G Quantum Communication Networks) and V4 (Standardization) also exhibited minor variations (Table 8).",
    "These discrepancies suggest a degree of divergence in the rank assignment between the two algorithms, which should be considered when identifying the most influential variables for 6G-SQC projects.",
    "In addition to Spearman's Rank-order correlation, we used an independent t-test to compare the mean rank differences produced by both algorithms (Table 9).",
    "The result from Levene's Test was non-significant (p = 0.745 > 0.05), indicating equal variances, and we continued with this assumption.",
    "The outcome of the t-test (t = 0.752, p = 0.502 > 0.05) indicated no substantial differences between the ranks generated by the two algorithms."
  ]
}